\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces The sodium mode softening. Effective zero-point frequency $\hbar \omega _{\mathrm  {eff}} =\hbar ^{2}/2M\langle \delta ^{2}\rangle _0$ of the quantized alkali mode, from an exact one-dimensional solution of the fitted wells at the physical masses. It collapses by three orders of magnitude across the transition, from a stiff $\sim 30$~meV single-well mode into a sub-{meV} soft mode as the gallery opens, entering a quantum-paraelectric window. Inset: the lowest levels in the $6.9$~\r A{} sodium double well, with the near-degenerate tunnelling doublet $E_0,E_1$ and the even overtone $E_2$ that carries the quadratic electron--phonon coupling.}}{4}{}}
\newlabel{fig:soft}{{4}{4}{}{}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {IV}The difficulty at 9.9 \r A{} and what it teaches}{4}{}}
\newlabel{sec:difficulty}{{IV}{4}{}{}{}}
